<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000467854"><TermName>palliation</TermName><TermPronunciation>(PA-lee-AY-shun)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>Relief of symptoms and suffering caused by cancer and other life-threatening diseases. Palliation helps a patient feel more comfortable and improves the quality of life, but does not cure the disease.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000717003" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;palliation&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000717002" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;paliación&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>paliación</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Alivio de los síntomas y el sufrimiento que causan el cáncer y otras enfermedades potencialmente mortales. La paliación ayuda al paciente a sentirse más cómodo y mejora la calidad de vida, pero no cura la enfermedad.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition><DateFirstPublished>2006-05-11</DateFirstPublished><RelatedInformation><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="en" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/care-choices/palliative-care-fact-sheet">Palliative Care in Cancer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="en" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping">Coping with Cancer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/espanol/cancer/cancer-avanzado/opciones-de-cuidado/hoja-informativa-cuidados-paliativos">Cuidados paliativos durante el cáncer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/espanol/cancer/sobrellevar">Cómo hacer frente al cáncer</RelatedExternalRef></RelatedInformation></GlossaryTerm>
